1
00:00:34,280 --> 00:00:35,520
What's that song called?

2
00:00:35,679 --> 00:00:38,119
The one everyone sang at Azha's wedding.

3
00:00:38,600 --> 00:00:40,119
Which one? Hum a few bars.

4
00:00:47,079 --> 00:00:48,119
Oh, I know.

5
00:00:52,719 --> 00:00:53,719
This...

6
00:01:05,079 --> 00:01:06,079
Hello?

7
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:07,120
Where are you?

8
00:01:07,280 --> 00:01:08,358
Just passed Xigui.

9
00:01:08,359 --> 00:01:09,479
You'll be there before dark.

10
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:54,680
What time will we get here?

11
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:58,280
Around nightfall.

12
00:01:59,280 --> 00:02:01,040
How am I supposed to
know when it gets dark?

13
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:05,680
Stop.

14
00:02:50,319 --> 00:02:51,319
Bro.

15
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:55,319
Is it okay if you stay
at my friend's place?

16
00:04:49,519 --> 00:04:50,720
Is the room ready?

17
00:04:50,879 --> 00:04:52,279
Yeah. How long is he staying?

18
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:54,120
He didn't say.

19
00:04:54,720 --> 00:04:56,000
He won't be staying long.

20
00:04:57,360 --> 00:04:59,519
Alright, just take him there first.

21
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:01,360
I'm off.

22
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:27,300
"A Winter Sun Wakes the Wind in Spring Hills' Dream"

23
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:34,500
(Episode 1: DJI)

24
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:47,720
Thanks for your hard work.

25
00:05:51,879 --> 00:05:53,278
This is the laundry room.

26
00:05:53,279 --> 00:05:54,480
This is the kitchen.

27
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:55,879
This is the dining room.

28
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:58,000
You can have tea here.

29
00:06:00,279 --> 00:06:01,519
Don't be picky.

30
00:06:02,279 --> 00:06:03,959
You're lucky to have a place to stay.

31
00:06:04,680 --> 00:06:06,359
And Brother Guo is in Shangjing.

32
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:08,696
You're slumming it in the tea
mountains without an assistant this time?

33
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:09,920
Aren't you my assistant?

34
00:06:10,759 --> 00:06:12,278
Let me make this clear.

35
00:06:12,279 --> 00:06:13,199
I'm your brother.

36
00:06:13,199 --> 00:06:14,199
Not your assistant.

37
00:06:15,519 --> 00:06:16,800
Brother equals assistant.

38
00:06:22,879 --> 00:06:24,519
When your assistant gets here, I'm out.

39
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:27,878
Take it. We're going to the master's
place tomorrow night to roast tea.

40
00:06:27,879 --> 00:06:28,879
Okay, I'm off.

41
00:06:56,399 --> 00:06:57,720
I'll show you to your room.

42
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:19,879
How old are you?

43
00:07:20,279 --> 00:07:21,279
18?

44
00:07:22,759 --> 00:07:23,800
You're asking me?

45
00:07:24,079 --> 00:07:25,079
Take a guess.

46
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:27,120
You look 80.

47
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:51,800
Uh, inside.

48
00:07:58,360 --> 00:07:59,360
Sister Lan.

49
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:00,560
Hey, Lu.

50
00:08:00,879 --> 00:08:02,136
There are two boxes of props over there.

51
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:03,719
Could you call the props
team to move them for me?

52
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:04,720
Okay.

53
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:16,480
Should I answer it?

54
00:08:17,759 --> 00:08:18,759
Who is it?

55
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:20,160
Sister Lan.

56
00:08:20,319 --> 00:08:21,319
Answer it.

57
00:08:22,800 --> 00:08:23,839
I'll hold it for you.

58
00:08:24,279 --> 00:08:25,279
Qinglang.

59
00:08:26,879 --> 00:08:29,399
Sister Lan, I'm in the shower.

60
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:31,160
You're in Molie?

61
00:08:31,279 --> 00:08:32,279
Just got here.

62
00:08:32,799 --> 00:08:33,799
Did you get carsick?

63
00:08:34,879 --> 00:08:36,799
Yeah, I was throwing up like crazy.

64
00:08:37,519 --> 00:08:38,960
Come back. There's water.

65
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,000
Is someone with you?

66
00:08:42,399 --> 00:08:43,960
Uh, Qingtian.

67
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:46,519
He's holding the phone for me.

68
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:47,679
Alright then.

69
00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:49,135
If you're not comfortable,
just stay for a couple of days.

70
00:08:49,159 --> 00:08:51,096
We need you for a cameo
in the scenes there next week.

71
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:52,919
About the variety show with Shi Yuhao...

72
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:54,158
If you have second thoughts, let me know.

73
00:08:54,159 --> 00:08:55,000
I'll handle it.

74
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:56,120
Okay.

75
00:09:11,919 --> 00:09:13,559
Lu, call the props team to move this.

76
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:16,720
Sister Lan, I don't want to be on set.

77
00:09:17,960 --> 00:09:19,158
Lang Di needs me.

78
00:09:19,159 --> 00:09:20,799
How can I not be by his side?

79
00:09:22,159 --> 00:09:23,600
Lang Di has a new assistant.

80
00:09:23,919 --> 00:09:25,679
Who knows Lang Di better than I do?

81
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,519
If I'm not with him,

82
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,159
he can't even eat or sleep properly.

83
00:09:30,399 --> 00:09:33,120
Alright, just take good
care of those two handfuls.

84
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:34,799
I couldn't care less about Qi Haoyu.

85
00:09:34,919 --> 00:09:36,158
He's not even with our agency.

86
00:09:36,159 --> 00:09:37,159
Don't be childish.

87
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:39,398
If we can't be childish now,
we'll be too old for it, Sister Lan.

88
00:09:39,399 --> 00:09:40,399
Mm.

89
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:42,495
Lang Di just agreed to do the variety show.

90
00:09:42,519 --> 00:09:44,359
Shi Yuhao will definitely
be haunting him now.

91
00:09:44,559 --> 00:09:46,359
I have to be by his
side at a time like this.

92
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:01,799
I'm going downstairs to cook.

93
00:10:03,399 --> 00:10:04,759
I'll call you when dinner's ready.

94
00:10:13,679 --> 00:10:14,679
Hello.

95
00:10:18,159 --> 00:10:20,360
Sorry, I don't drink iced beverages.

96
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:22,919
The actors have left for the set.

97
00:10:26,919 --> 00:10:27,919
Cut the act.

98
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:31,239
Are you out of your mind?

99
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:33,879
Why would you do a
variety show with Shi Yuhao?

100
00:10:34,679 --> 00:10:36,720
Lang Di, are you being held hostage?

101
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:39,199
Ah, this is great!

102
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:41,919
My Leopard and Kitty are reuniting!

103
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:44,199
Bro, are you short on cash?

104
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:45,639
To think you'd even take this show.

105
00:10:46,360 --> 00:10:49,359
Bro, did the agency
make you take this show?

106
00:10:49,360 --> 00:10:51,799
I don't want to see you
get used by Shi Yuhao again.

107
00:10:53,919 --> 00:10:56,359
A seven-year love affair
ends for a new flame.

108
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:58,000
Ah, I'm going crazy!

109
00:11:06,679 --> 00:11:08,200
Do you need help getting dressed?

110
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:11,720
Mm.

111
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:16,600
Mm.

112
00:11:42,396 --> 00:11:50,103
[A string of unintelligble
hashtags on Weibo maybe?]

113
00:11:53,356 --> 00:11:55,463
[Xu the God of Wealth is calling]

114
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:08,000
Are you okay?

115
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:10,360
I heard you went into the
mountains with Qingtian.

116
00:12:14,529 --> 00:12:17,116
[Shi Yuhao is calling]

117
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:41,960
If you hadn't answered, I
was about to come find you.

118
00:12:48,679 --> 00:12:49,679
Brother Guo.

119
00:12:50,080 --> 00:12:51,558
Oh, Sister Lan.

120
00:12:51,559 --> 00:12:52,719
Oh, Sister Lan, hello.

121
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:53,200
I've heard so much about you.

122
00:12:53,201 --> 00:12:54,921
Hello, hello. Thank you for your hard work.

123
00:12:55,519 --> 00:12:56,960
This kid insisted on going to Molie.

124
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:02,720
Brother Guo, go get Han Lu's costume ready.

125
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:05,600
Han Lu.

126
00:13:07,919 --> 00:13:09,278
I was just on the phone with him.

127
00:13:09,279 --> 00:13:10,720
I heard a stranger's voice with him.

128
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,159
He said it was Qingtian.

129
00:13:12,360 --> 00:13:13,960
But the voice didn't sound like him.

130
00:13:14,679 --> 00:13:16,759
Did Qingtian tell you who's
hosting them over there?

131
00:13:16,919 --> 00:13:18,720
They're all Qingtian's tea farmer friends.

132
00:13:18,879 --> 00:13:19,879
Is it safe?

133
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:21,895
No one's chasing
celebrities in the mountains.

134
00:13:21,919 --> 00:13:23,799
Oh, that's good. I'll let
you get back to work.

135
00:13:36,120 --> 00:13:37,559
Bro, let me.

136
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:46,239
Qingtian said he's not with you.

137
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:47,440
So where are you staying?

138
00:13:53,080 --> 00:13:54,320
At a villager's house.

139
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,200
Is it safe?

140
00:14:14,559 --> 00:14:15,559
What about dinner?

141
00:14:24,159 --> 00:14:26,399
You were sleeping so soundly,
I didn't want to wake you.

142
00:14:33,519 --> 00:14:35,279
Hey, you changed your clothes.

143
00:14:35,799 --> 00:14:37,759
I only wear pajamas when I sleep.

144
00:14:42,720 --> 00:14:44,320
How did my clothes get changed?

145
00:14:45,519 --> 00:14:46,519
How would I know?

146
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:52,120
I'm hungry.

147
00:15:00,039 --> 00:15:01,655
Be careful what you eat in the mountains.

148
00:15:01,679 --> 00:15:02,519
You have a sensitive stomach.

149
00:15:02,520 --> 00:15:04,040
You'll throw up if you don't eat well.

150
00:15:04,559 --> 00:15:06,279
I hear the food there is on the spicy side.

151
00:15:06,519 --> 00:15:08,039
Tell Qingtian to go easy on the spice.

152
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:10,560
Qingtian isn't cooking for me.

153
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:13,440
Who is, then?

154
00:15:14,759 --> 00:15:15,759
My assistant.

155
00:15:18,039 --> 00:15:19,479
Brother Guo being there is fine too.

156
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:26,480
Come down.

157
00:16:50,919 --> 00:16:51,600
I heated it up in the microwave.

158
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:52,600
See if it's too hot.

159
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:56,120
Let go.

160
00:17:05,680 --> 00:17:06,680
You want me to feed you?

161
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:08,480
Mm-hmm.

162
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:15,920
Open your mouth.

163
00:17:17,160 --> 00:17:18,160
Wider.

164
00:17:41,759 --> 00:17:42,759
Mm.

165
00:18:50,920 --> 00:18:52,079
Tea or coffee?

166
00:18:52,559 --> 00:18:53,680
They have coffee here?

167
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:55,480
They produce both tea and coffee here.

168
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:56,960
Whatever.

169
00:18:57,519 --> 00:18:58,719
They don't produce 'whatever'.

170
00:19:07,519 --> 00:19:08,519
Qinglang, talk to me.

171
00:19:10,680 --> 00:19:11,680
Before we film the show,

172
00:19:11,681 --> 00:19:13,118
if you harass me again,

173
00:19:13,119 --> 00:19:14,160
I'll break the contract.

174
00:19:15,319 --> 00:19:16,399
I'm not trying to harass you.

175
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:17,359
I'm just worried about you.

176
00:19:17,359 --> 00:19:18,359
Worried about what?

177
00:19:18,799 --> 00:19:19,519
I know you.

178
00:19:19,520 --> 00:19:20,919
You agreed to do this show so readily.

179
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:22,279
Isn't this what you wanted?

180
00:19:22,519 --> 00:19:23,896
You want to have your cake and eat it too.

181
00:19:23,920 --> 00:19:26,079
The way you're acting
right now disgusts me.

182
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,000
We can't sort this out over the phone.

183
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:30,000
Where are you?

184
00:19:30,001 --> 00:19:31,920
I'm in hell. Come and get me if you dare.

185
00:19:36,709 --> 00:19:38,603
[Zhang Fengdan is calling]

186
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:42,279
Hello, Sister Dan.

187
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:44,639
I'm on set.

188
00:19:44,640 --> 00:19:46,640
Shooting a short commercial.

189
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:06,519
Hey, Yuhao's back.

190
00:20:08,920 --> 00:20:11,480
Yuhao, when are you and
Qinglang doing that variety show?

191
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:23,759
My house is hell?

192
00:20:34,319 --> 00:20:35,680
Tea... coffee.

193
00:21:06,880 --> 00:21:07,920
What's your name?

194
00:21:08,920 --> 00:21:09,920
Xu Changyang.

195
00:21:12,319 --> 00:21:13,799
You've always lived in the mountains?

196
00:21:14,799 --> 00:21:15,799
Eight years.

197
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:19,640
Came to the mountains when I was 10.

198
00:21:20,119 --> 00:21:21,119
12.

199
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:25,480
So you're 20 this year.

200
00:21:28,519 --> 00:21:29,999
It'll get cold if you don't drink it.

201
00:21:31,759 --> 00:21:33,680
Didn't I say I wanted tea?

202
00:21:35,359 --> 00:21:37,159
Your first choice isn't
always the right one.

203
00:21:37,279 --> 00:21:38,920
What you really want is coffee.

204
00:21:45,599 --> 00:21:47,176
You don't have to wash
the cup when you're done.

205
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:48,896
If you're tired, go to your room and sleep.

206
00:21:48,920 --> 00:21:50,920
When you wake up, call
Qingtian if you need me.

207
00:21:52,599 --> 00:21:53,960
Going to see Qingtian this late?

208
00:21:57,119 --> 00:21:59,160
Yeah, he's definitely still awake.

209
00:22:00,279 --> 00:22:01,279
I'm off.

210
00:22:08,799 --> 00:22:11,599
Lang Di, you can't just get rid of me.

211
00:22:11,880 --> 00:22:14,240
Sister Lan said you have a new assistant.

212
00:22:14,480 --> 00:22:16,199
What kind of considerate person
could you find in the village?

213
00:22:16,200 --> 00:22:17,760
They're all just a bunch of rough guys.

214
00:22:17,880 --> 00:22:19,520
How could they possibly take care of you?

215
00:22:19,799 --> 00:22:21,920
I told Sister Lan to let me go.

216
00:22:21,960 --> 00:22:23,936
But Sister Lan insisted on
keeping me with the film crew.

217
00:22:23,960 --> 00:22:24,920
If you just say the word...

218
00:22:24,921 --> 00:22:27,561
I'd run over there even if the
mountain road had a thousand turns.

219
00:22:31,279 --> 00:22:33,119
If you came, I'd have to take care of you.

220
00:22:33,279 --> 00:22:34,558
Just stay put with the crew.

221
00:22:34,559 --> 00:22:35,759
I'll be back next week.

222
00:22:36,279 --> 00:22:39,599
There's always another
'next week.' I don't want that.

223
00:22:40,319 --> 00:22:41,559
Are you coming or not?

224
00:22:42,559 --> 00:22:44,400
Oh, I hear someone talking.

225
00:22:44,599 --> 00:22:46,319
Lang Di, what are you doing?

226
00:22:46,519 --> 00:22:48,079
Are you really getting rid of me?

227
00:22:48,319 --> 00:22:50,000
Sister Lan said you have a new assistant.

228
00:22:50,119 --> 00:22:51,160
Is it true?

229
00:22:51,319 --> 00:22:52,960
Alright, stop the drama.

230
00:22:53,119 --> 00:22:55,079
You sound like you're
in a palace drama.

231
00:22:58,920 --> 00:23:00,079
I can go too.

232
00:23:27,319 --> 00:23:28,519
The fresh aroma is coming out.

233
00:23:32,119 --> 00:23:33,359
Lower the heat, lower the heat.

234
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:40,400
Is Teacher Fu's place far from here?

235
00:23:40,480 --> 00:23:41,920
Not too far, not too close.

236
00:23:50,319 --> 00:23:52,519
How are you so sure
he's not asleep this late?

237
00:23:52,920 --> 00:23:54,255
It's like this every time
we come to the mountains.

238
00:23:54,279 --> 00:23:56,176
The first night, he always
drags me along to roast tea.

239
00:23:56,200 --> 00:23:57,479
This time, it's because you're here...

240
00:23:57,480 --> 00:23:59,456
that he told me to come
over tomorrow night instead.

241
00:23:59,480 --> 00:24:00,799
The tea you roast is delicious.

242
00:24:01,880 --> 00:24:03,279
You must have tried it, right?

243
00:24:03,720 --> 00:24:05,680
No, you just gave me coffee.

244
00:24:11,519 --> 00:24:12,440
That's good, master.

245
00:24:12,519 --> 00:24:13,519
Okay.

246
00:24:23,849 --> 00:24:26,669
[I'm guessing he's blocking
the person he just had sex with]

247
00:24:35,759 --> 00:24:37,000
Qingtian, Teacher Fu.

248
00:24:40,559 --> 00:24:41,559
So many people.

249
00:24:42,279 --> 00:24:43,279
Hey, Azha.

250
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:45,400
Have a seat.

251
00:24:46,519 --> 00:24:47,960
Qingtian, is this your brother?

252
00:24:48,279 --> 00:24:49,639
The big star is good-looking, huh?

253
00:24:50,279 --> 00:24:51,359
Do you know him?

254
00:24:54,279 --> 00:24:55,439
What's the deal with you two?

255
00:24:56,519 --> 00:24:57,519
Drink up, drink up.

256
00:24:58,319 --> 00:24:59,919
Teacher Fu, is this batch done roasting?

257
00:25:05,279 --> 00:25:06,879
With Molie's liquor, once you
have a sip, you have to keep drinking.

258
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:07,880
Can you handle it?

259
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:09,160
Keep drinking until when?

260
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:10,519
Until you pass out.

261
00:25:28,279 --> 00:25:28,920
Teacher Fu.

262
00:25:28,920 --> 00:25:29,920
Hmm?

263
00:25:30,480 --> 00:25:31,960
Is that the tea you picked yesterday?

264
00:25:51,920 --> 00:25:53,559
I always see you in the media.

265
00:25:54,119 --> 00:25:54,759
Teacher Fu.

266
00:25:54,759 --> 00:25:55,160
Yes?

267
00:25:55,161 --> 00:25:56,719
The tea you gave Qingtian before...

268
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:57,559
I really liked it.

269
00:25:57,599 --> 00:25:58,799
Sister Lan liked it a lot too.

270
00:25:59,480 --> 00:26:01,119
Oh? Which one did you like?

271
00:26:01,799 --> 00:26:02,880
It was a ripe pu'er.

272
00:26:03,319 --> 00:26:05,118
Sister Lan and I both
have sensitive stomachs.

273
00:26:05,119 --> 00:26:06,279
So ripe tea suits us better.

274
00:26:06,519 --> 00:26:07,519
The aroma is coming out.

275
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:10,600
Teacher Fu, come have a drink.

276
00:26:11,799 --> 00:26:12,799
I'll toast to you.

277
00:26:13,119 --> 00:26:14,119
Thank you.

278
00:26:30,480 --> 00:26:31,480
Want to try?

279
00:26:31,799 --> 00:26:32,799
Sure.

280
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:35,920
Put on the gloves.

281
00:26:52,279 --> 00:26:53,919
How long does it take to roast one batch?

282
00:26:54,519 --> 00:26:55,720
At least half an hour.

283
00:26:56,799 --> 00:26:57,799
It's hard work.

284
00:26:58,799 --> 00:27:00,118
That's why Qingtian can't do it.

285
00:27:00,119 --> 00:27:01,719
He always makes Teacher Fu and me do it.

286
00:27:10,400 --> 00:27:11,480
It smells amazing.

287
00:27:11,599 --> 00:27:14,176
This is the first time I've smelled
the aroma of tea at this stage.

288
00:27:14,200 --> 00:27:15,680
It smells even better than it tastes.

289
00:27:16,680 --> 00:27:18,400
The aroma is different at every stage.

290
00:27:44,279 --> 00:27:45,920
I'll roll the tea I roasted myself.

291
00:27:47,079 --> 00:27:48,279
You teach him.

292
00:27:50,880 --> 00:27:53,200
Do you always fight with your
brother over things at home?

293
00:27:53,799 --> 00:27:55,839
Do I look like I have
nothing better to do at home?

294
00:27:56,279 --> 00:27:58,200
Shake it. Let the heat out.

295
00:27:59,599 --> 00:28:00,879
Save this batch of tea for me.

296
00:28:00,880 --> 00:28:03,000
- I'll drink it myself.
- It's very expensive.

297
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:05,720
- I'll pay.
- I'm not kidding.

298
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:07,280
The tea Qingtian had me roast...

299
00:28:07,319 --> 00:28:08,680
the leaves are all top-grade.

300
00:28:08,799 --> 00:28:10,399
The market price is 80,000 per kilogram.

301
00:28:10,559 --> 00:28:12,079
At auction, it could go for a million.

302
00:28:13,279 --> 00:28:15,039
And if you say I'm the
one who roasted it...

303
00:28:15,200 --> 00:28:16,880
it would sell for at least ten million.

304
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:18,680
So, I'll sell it to you for eight million.

305
00:28:18,799 --> 00:28:20,400
You'll make a clean two million profit.

306
00:28:21,880 --> 00:28:22,880
Hey, that's expensive.

307
00:28:30,119 --> 00:28:31,799
When are you two having kids?

308
00:28:32,680 --> 00:28:33,759
Tomorrow is the 15th.

309
00:28:34,599 --> 00:28:36,000
No one's going to sleep, huh.

310
00:28:38,519 --> 00:28:40,359
That's how it is during
the spring tea season.

311
00:28:40,480 --> 00:28:41,559
We roast tea until dawn.

312
00:28:41,680 --> 00:28:42,720
Go back, get some sleep.

313
00:28:42,920 --> 00:28:44,095
Then go up the mountain to pick more tea.

314
00:28:44,119 --> 00:28:45,519
If you're tired, go back and sleep.

315
00:28:46,880 --> 00:28:47,880
What about you?

316
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:51,680
I'll walk you back.

317
00:28:52,079 --> 00:28:53,680
How can you come to Molie and not drink?

318
00:28:53,799 --> 00:28:55,720
Have one drink. I'll take you back after.

319
00:28:56,279 --> 00:28:57,279
Alright.

320
00:28:58,559 --> 00:28:59,559
What kind of liquor?

321
00:29:00,079 --> 00:29:00,880
Mulberry wine.

322
00:29:00,920 --> 00:29:02,160
Let's do an 'aerial refueling'.

323
00:29:02,200 --> 00:29:03,319
Aerial refueling.

324
00:29:03,559 --> 00:29:04,559
Aerial refueling.

325
00:29:04,920 --> 00:29:05,960
Aerial refueling.

326
00:29:08,720 --> 00:29:10,480
Aerial refueling. Chug!

327
00:29:10,799 --> 00:29:18,799
Chug!

328
00:29:30,319 --> 00:29:31,480
This isn't fruit wine.

329
00:29:32,559 --> 00:29:34,319
It's mulberry baijiu. 52% alcohol.

330
00:29:39,200 --> 00:29:39,880
This shirt...

331
00:29:39,881 --> 00:29:41,799
Hey, my brother's a one-drink wonder.

332
00:29:42,599 --> 00:29:43,599
Don't be ridiculous.

333
00:29:43,759 --> 00:29:44,759
Here, you take it.

334
00:29:49,680 --> 00:29:50,680
See you tomorrow.

335
00:29:50,759 --> 00:29:51,759
See you tomorrow.

336
00:29:54,279 --> 00:29:57,160
A call is coming in. Don't answer it.

337
00:30:00,079 --> 00:30:01,200
We'll drink more later.

338
00:30:01,319 --> 00:30:02,319
Okay.

339
00:30:10,759 --> 00:30:12,480
Shi Yuhao, you bastard.

340
00:30:14,119 --> 00:30:15,279
Come on, drink.

341
00:30:21,079 --> 00:30:22,079
Lie down.

342
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:27,160
When he drinks too much,
he thinks he's the boss.

343
00:30:28,079 --> 00:30:30,119
Shi Yuhao, you bastard.

344
00:30:33,559 --> 00:30:34,680
Still feeling sick?

345
00:30:35,680 --> 00:30:36,200
Trash can.

346
00:30:36,200 --> 00:30:37,200
Qingtian, the trash can.

347
00:31:12,920 --> 00:31:15,359
You were pretty young
seven years ago, weren't you?

348
00:31:16,119 --> 00:31:17,759
I'm only a year older than you.

349
00:31:22,319 --> 00:31:24,199
My brother is never short
of people around him.

350
00:31:24,680 --> 00:31:26,759
I've never felt that
he's truly loved anyone.

351
00:31:29,799 --> 00:31:32,319
He seems to have a very
complicated history with Shi Yuhao.

352
00:31:33,480 --> 00:31:35,279
But I don't think he ever truly loved him.

353
00:31:37,400 --> 00:31:38,680
There's a lot of gossip online.

354
00:31:39,279 --> 00:31:42,119
They say he started avoiding Shi
Yuhao as a form of self-preservation.

355
00:31:43,079 --> 00:31:44,720
Because he knew he would fall in love.

356
00:31:44,960 --> 00:31:46,440
And he was afraid of falling in love.

357
00:31:46,920 --> 00:31:47,960
That's why he avoided him.

358
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:56,279
How many people really
understand love at that age?

359
00:31:57,720 --> 00:31:59,000
A moment of impulse...

360
00:31:59,720 --> 00:32:01,000
a fleeting crush.

361
00:32:02,119 --> 00:32:03,519
Everyone goes through that.

362
00:32:06,079 --> 00:32:07,079
Changyang.

363
00:32:08,200 --> 00:32:09,880
I consider you a good friend.

364
00:32:10,319 --> 00:32:11,919
So I want to give you a piece of advice.

365
00:32:14,759 --> 00:32:16,279
Ever since Shi Yuhao...

366
00:32:16,920 --> 00:32:19,160
my brother won't let
himself get hurt again.

367
00:32:21,319 --> 00:32:22,519
You need to know your limits.

368
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:27,559
He's asleep.

369
00:32:27,680 --> 00:32:29,160
Let me help you straighten him out.

370
00:32:29,480 --> 00:32:30,480
Just let him be.

371
00:32:31,079 --> 00:32:32,278
You should go back and rest.

372
00:32:32,279 --> 00:32:33,839
We have to go up the mountain tomorrow.

373
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:39,559
- I'm leaving.
- Help me draw the curtains.

374
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:34,278
I'm out of face masks.

375
00:33:34,279 --> 00:33:35,279
Lend me a face mask.

376
00:33:35,720 --> 00:33:36,799
What's your name?

377
00:33:37,119 --> 00:33:38,119
Me?

378
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:40,200
My name is Qi Haoyu.

379
00:33:43,079 --> 00:33:44,079
Brother Guo.

380
00:33:47,920 --> 00:33:51,519
Brother Guo lent Qi Haoyu one
face mask. When will it be returned?

381
00:33:52,119 --> 00:33:53,598
Three days. I just placed an order.

382
00:33:53,599 --> 00:33:54,679
It'll arrive in three days.

383
00:33:57,000 --> 00:33:58,880
You have to give me back the same brand.

384
00:33:59,279 --> 00:34:00,479
Then I'll place another order.

385
00:34:03,279 --> 00:34:04,279
Bro.

386
00:34:04,720 --> 00:34:06,680
He's the actor who has scenes with me.

387
00:34:07,480 --> 00:34:10,000
Han Lu. You two said hi
in the group chat, right?

388
00:34:10,920 --> 00:34:13,079
He seemed pretty
friendly in the group chat.

389
00:34:14,719 --> 00:34:16,320
He's pretty friendly to me too.

390
00:34:17,960 --> 00:34:20,559
Then what did I do to get on his bad side?

391
00:34:32,119 --> 00:34:34,000
Do you understand the
lines for the next scene?

392
00:34:34,599 --> 00:34:36,079
It's written in the director's notes.

393
00:34:36,900 --> 00:34:39,100
Just because it's written
doesn't mean I understand it.

394
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:40,400
Do you get it?

395
00:34:44,079 --> 00:34:45,079
Explain it to me.

396
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:49,920
Existence is existence.

397
00:34:50,719 --> 00:34:52,599
That's a very extreme perspective.

398
00:34:54,360 --> 00:34:56,320
My appearance is a form of existence.

399
00:34:56,519 --> 00:34:58,319
Whether it's extreme
or not is your judgment.

400
00:34:58,719 --> 00:35:01,559
My existence has nothing
to do with your judgment.

401
00:35:05,679 --> 00:35:07,119
This flavor is low-grade.

402
00:35:07,360 --> 00:35:10,000
But my judgment can't
change the fact that it's coffee.

403
00:35:10,960 --> 00:35:12,280
Existence is existence.

404
00:35:12,320 --> 00:35:13,320
Understand now?

405
00:35:15,920 --> 00:35:17,400
You don't speak like a normal person.

406
00:35:20,480 --> 00:35:21,640
What's so low-class about it?

407
00:35:21,880 --> 00:35:22,880
It tastes pretty good.

408
00:35:34,569 --> 00:35:39,543
[TN: He's looking up a comment section about
the actor passed out next to him and his "ex"]

409
00:35:39,729 --> 00:35:44,476
[The comments are discussing the two of them
reuiniting on the variety show scheduled to film]

410
00:35:44,541 --> 00:35:51,256
[Some fans are very "leave him alone," some fans
are excited about them getting back together]

411
00:35:51,280 --> 00:35:59,707
[Some fans say "no way it will ever happen," some
are like "I heard his manager blah blah blah"]

412
00:35:59,731 --> 00:36:07,604
[Some fans are talking about it from an economic
perspective, it just goes on and on and on]

413
00:36:20,719 --> 00:36:21,719
What time is it?

414
00:36:22,039 --> 00:36:23,039
4:00.

415
00:36:24,840 --> 00:36:25,840
It's still early.

416
00:36:26,639 --> 00:36:27,639
In the afternoon.

417
00:36:31,800 --> 00:36:34,199
I slept from last night
until this afternoon?

418
00:36:34,639 --> 00:36:36,239
You can't remember a thing after drinking?

419
00:36:37,440 --> 00:36:39,598
- Yeah.
- You really were drinking.

420
00:36:39,599 --> 00:36:40,599
Mmm.

421
00:36:40,920 --> 00:36:42,000
What's this?

422
00:36:42,320 --> 00:36:43,320
My clothes.

423
00:36:48,079 --> 00:36:49,119
Are you sore?

424
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:51,840
It's your first time roasting tea.

425
00:36:51,841 --> 00:36:53,001
It'd be weird if you weren't.

426
00:36:56,599 --> 00:36:57,599
Want to sleep some more?

427
00:37:00,719 --> 00:37:02,199
I could sleep a little longer.

428
00:37:42,199 --> 00:37:43,199
What are you doing?

429
00:37:43,719 --> 00:37:44,719
What do you want to do?

430
00:37:45,480 --> 00:37:47,199
Shouldn't I be the one asking you that?

431
00:37:47,840 --> 00:37:48,840
Lie on your stomach.

432
00:38:01,280 --> 00:38:02,320
I haven't showered yet.

433
00:38:06,440 --> 00:38:08,040
I'm allergic to a lot of essential oils.

434
00:38:10,280 --> 00:38:11,920
You won't be allergic to tea tree oil.

435
00:38:12,039 --> 00:38:14,400
Ow, ow, ow, that hurts!

436
00:38:32,320 --> 00:38:34,840
Wow, your technique is
pretty good. Did you study this?

437
00:38:35,840 --> 00:38:37,680
I once saved the last
wolf in these mountains.

438
00:38:39,440 --> 00:38:40,639
Have you ever saved a bear?

439
00:38:41,480 --> 00:38:42,480
I'm saving one right now.

440
00:38:44,039 --> 00:38:45,519
Hold still, big bear.

441
00:38:49,920 --> 00:38:51,199
Why was it the last wolf?

442
00:38:51,840 --> 00:38:53,439
The year I first came to these mountains,

443
00:38:53,440 --> 00:38:54,600
there were still wolves here.

444
00:38:55,079 --> 00:38:58,280
Later, the locals started
putting poison on their poultry.

445
00:38:58,519 --> 00:39:00,079
Any wolf that ate it would be poisoned.

446
00:39:00,440 --> 00:39:01,840
When one wolf died,

447
00:39:01,880 --> 00:39:03,840
the others would come and eat its carcass.

448
00:39:04,519 --> 00:39:06,840
That's how the entire pack was wiped out.

449
00:39:07,639 --> 00:39:09,480
I came across one of them on the mountain.

450
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:12,280
I actually used tea tree oil to
try and counteract the poison.

451
00:39:12,880 --> 00:39:14,840
I never found out if it survived.

452
00:39:15,079 --> 00:39:16,280
I never saw it again.

453
00:39:16,639 --> 00:39:19,199
So, to me, that was the last wolf.

454
00:39:22,000 --> 00:39:23,400
When a wolf dies, it gets eaten.

455
00:39:23,920 --> 00:39:25,440
When a person dies, they get buried.

456
00:39:26,599 --> 00:39:28,119
That's the progress of civilization.

457
00:39:29,239 --> 00:39:30,239
Not necessarily.

458
00:39:30,719 --> 00:39:32,280
Civilization can regress at any moment.

459
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:34,639
It depends on where a person dies.

460
00:39:34,800 --> 00:39:35,960
And under what circumstances.

461
00:39:37,079 --> 00:39:39,159
Survival is the basic
instinct of all living things.

462
00:39:39,440 --> 00:39:41,879
You can see it everywhere in this forest.

463
00:39:41,880 --> 00:39:43,039
This instinct is everywhere.

464
00:39:43,800 --> 00:39:45,199
Love is a human instinct.

465
00:39:46,920 --> 00:39:48,599
I don't know what counts as love.

466
00:39:48,639 --> 00:39:50,000
You should know all about it.

467
00:39:51,840 --> 00:39:53,000
I don't know either.

468
00:40:04,719 --> 00:40:06,599
You used too much brute
force roasting the tea.

469
00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:10,199
I do everything that way.

470
00:40:15,840 --> 00:40:17,200
I'll call you when dinner's ready.

471
00:40:36,239 --> 00:40:37,400
I'll help.

472
00:40:47,199 --> 00:40:48,280
Go play on your phone.

473
00:40:49,800 --> 00:40:52,000
Or go get the drone
back from Qingtian's place.

474
00:40:56,880 --> 00:40:58,480
Why were you carrying a drone yesterday?

475
00:40:58,719 --> 00:41:00,038
I was going to take
you to film the sunrise.

476
00:41:00,039 --> 00:41:01,280
But then you got drunk.

477
00:41:04,880 --> 00:41:06,280
So that drone yesterday was yours?

478
00:41:06,800 --> 00:41:07,800
Yeah.

479
00:41:08,119 --> 00:41:09,639
So you filmed me throwing up, too?

480
00:41:10,119 --> 00:41:11,119
Did I?

481
00:41:29,400 --> 00:41:30,719
The footage is on my computer.

482
00:41:37,280 --> 00:41:38,840
My door is locked.

483
00:41:45,639 --> 00:41:46,639
The key?

484
00:41:47,599 --> 00:41:49,000
It's hanging right next to my door.

485
00:41:50,719 --> 00:41:51,719
Hey!

486
00:41:55,679 --> 00:41:57,839
Are all you celebrities this
worried about your image?

487
00:41:59,000 --> 00:42:00,319
If you dare post that
embarrassing footage of me,

488
00:42:00,320 --> 00:42:01,440
you're dead meat.

489
00:43:09,840 --> 00:43:10,840
Eat slowly.

490
00:43:16,280 --> 00:43:18,280
When you're done, I'll
take you out for a reshoot.

491
00:46:10,599 --> 00:46:11,440
Hello?

492
00:46:11,440 --> 00:46:12,119
Where are you?

493
00:46:12,119 --> 00:46:13,119
Just passed Xigui.

494
00:46:14,360 --> 00:46:15,440
You'll be here before dark.

495
00:46:57,000 --> 00:47:01,400
(Someone will always come into your life.)
